==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Anisyl
<hw>An"i*syl</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Org. Chem.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>The univalent radical, <chform>CH3.O.C6H4-</chform>,
of which anisol is the hydride.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The univalent
radical <chform>CH3.O.C6H4.CH2-</chform>; <as>as, <ex>anisyl</ex>
alcohol</as>.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>The univalent radical
<chform>CH3.O.C6H4.CO-</chform>, of anisic acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

